1
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:08,166
We hear many things 
from the scriptures.

2
00:00:08,166 --> 00:00:11,984
It’s, you know, infinite revelation,
revelation of the infinite.

3
00:00:11,984 --> 00:00:15,570
Āmnāyaḥ prāha tattvaṁ harim iha paramaṁ
(Śri Daśa-Mūla), etc.

4
00:00:15,864 --> 00:00:18,265
[Conceptual Liquid Sweetness]

5
00:00:18,435 --> 00:00:26,138
We can’t expect to readily
always fully understand that.

6
00:00:26,138 --> 00:00:29,668
But if we’re faithful and dedicated,

7
00:00:29,668 --> 00:00:34,649
in time, according to the heart’s
inner necessity,

8
00:00:34,649 --> 00:00:40,176
according to our modest natural growth
and development,

9
00:00:40,176 --> 00:00:44,207
something may come to us;
some understanding,

10
00:00:44,207 --> 00:00:48,708
an epiphany is also possible.

11
00:00:48,708 --> 00:00:49,990
So what did it say there?

12
00:00:49,990 --> 00:00:56,691
It is not as important understanding the meaning,
as to continually hear.

13
00:00:56,691 --> 00:00:59,030
Continuous hearing.

14
00:00:59,030 --> 00:01:01,271
And again Guru Mahārāj,
noted for his use of example,

15
00:01:01,271 --> 00:01:08,432
he said, he compared it to
ice, and ice melting.

16
00:01:08,432 --> 00:01:14,174
So ice being in this context
the rigid position,

17
00:01:14,174 --> 00:01:18,894
but in time it starts to melt
and achieve a liquid form.

18
00:01:18,894 --> 00:01:22,271
So some of these concepts,

19
00:01:22,271 --> 00:01:26,678
they appear to be impenetrable
or unapproachable

20
00:01:26,678 --> 00:01:28,535
at first, in the beginning.

21
00:01:28,535 --> 00:01:31,667
But in time they soften,

22
00:01:31,667 --> 00:01:34,918
and we could say,
just to continue the conceit,

23
00:01:34,918 --> 00:01:38,677
their liquid sweetness

24
00:01:38,677 --> 00:01:41,890
reveals itself in time. Rasa.

